Articles.Content:
I play god and found a race of intelligent organisms called humans, who take over KSP and put their universe into a video game.

My human race.

I create my own nation and populate half of the world; I let @TheEpicSquared have the other half since I don't want to rule the entire world. Could you imagine the headache that must be?!

My half of a planet

I accept @DarkOwl57's offer.

My half of a planet

I just open sfs file and clean away those two overlords of the Earth.
Then reload. Just initialized noone's world.

Here I am. Here's my hill.

See it? No. That's good. Therefore, you cannot destroy it. For what you do not see you cannot destroy. Unless you shoot a .22 with your eyes closed and it ricochets off a tree, then a birdbath, and then finally your grandma's wind chime.

I edited @kerbiloid's sfs file and brought back my and @TheEpicSquared's Empires.

Our empires

@The Raging Sandwich still has a cloaked hill. I use one of my spare keys to get in, then pull out my fourth-wall-breaking equipment and lock the .sfs out for everyone else.

My hill, shared with @The Raging Sandwich,  @DarkOwl57 and @TheEpicSquared's equally divided world.

Edited January 31, 2017 by greenTurtle1134
Fix mentions.

Too bad the key hole is left open. I shrink through the keyhole and take back the hill.

My hill, NOT shared with @The Raging Sandwich, @DarkOwl57 and @TheEpicSquared's equally divided world.

I take back every bit of land you took and it's now mine.

My half of a planet

Through brutal military conquest that lasted hundreds of years...

Spoiler

I take over the giant ant hill in my back yard.

i use that place on the internet where you can speak about politics, religion and sex

this is facebook, not mine place or hill, still i can't log there for now
